text: Stratford-Keppoch is a provincial electoral district for the Legislative Assembly of Prince Edward Island, Canada. The district was contested for the first time in the 2019 Prince Edward Island general election, and was created from a portion of the former district of Stratford-Kinlock. ==Members== The riding has elected the following Members of the Legislative Assembly: {| class="wikitable" align=centre !colspan=5|Members of the Legislative Assembly for Stratford-Keppoch |- !Assembly !Years !colspan="2"|Member !Party |- |66th |2019–present || |James Aylward |Progressive Conservative |} ==Election results== ==References== Category:Prince Edward Island provincial electoral districts
